frameDefinitions: These are words relating to emptying containers and clearing areas of some substance or items.
An Item is in a state of dryness.
These are words relating to filling containers and covering areas with some thing, things or substance, the Theme.
In this frame, which is a  part of the Trial sequence, a Judge gives a Finding with respect to the Charges against the Defendant in a particular Case.
An Agent affects an Artifact so that it is no longer capable of performing its inherent function.
frameExamples: The players <t>emptied</t> the bucket over his head.
Lionel Hutz <t>coated</t> the wall with paint.
He was <t>convicted</t> of fraud by Judge Judy.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Agent</fen> is the entity that does the emptying.
The <fen>Theme</fen>, when overtly expressed, invariably occurs in a PP Complement headed by 'of'.
The <fen>Source</fen> is the region or container which is emptied of something.  In this frame, the <fen>Source</fen> occurs as an NP Object.
The <fen>Cause</fen> is the non-sentient force which instigates the emptying.
The time at which the emptying takes place.
The location where the emptying takes place.
The <fen>Item</fen> exists in a state of dryness.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the actor who instigates the filling.
The <fen>Theme</fen> is the physical object or substance which changes location.
The <fen>Goal</fen> is the area or container being filled. Goal is generally the NP Object in this frame.
An event which brings about the filling of the <fen>Goal</fen>.
When the filling occurs.
Where the filling takes place.
The <fen>Judge</fen> (which may be the jury, judge, magistrate or court) decides on the <fen>Finding</fen>.
This role identifies the outcome of the <fen>Judge</fen>'s deliberation or consideration. Many LUs in this frame incorporate this FE.
The person who stands accused of a crime and is subject to the verdict.
This role refers to the <fen>Charges</fen> with respect to which the verdict is being given.
The <fen>Case</fen> on which the verdict is being given.
When the event occurs.
Where the event takes place.
The sentient entity causes the Artifact to not function.
The device that no longer works.
An inanimate entity or force that renders the <fen>Artifact</fen> non-functional.
The time at which the event takes place.
The place at which the event takes place.
listRoleExamples: <fex>A basic washing</fex> can degrease your workclothes.
The prisoners were deloused <fex>in June and August</fex>.
Rev. Lovejoy carefully brushed the rolls <fex>with butter</fex>.
